byline.contributor: Heba Afify contributed reporting from Cairo.

abstract: Defeat and subsequent death of Col Muammar el-Qaddafi makes Libya the third Arab country in 2011 to topple a longtime ruler; Qaddafi's violent death raises questions about how other embattled autocrats will respond to uprisings in their countries.
snippet: Of all the Arab despots who have lost power this year, Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi, typically, made the most dramatic exit.
